div.p:
This was the ancient Catholick Doctrine;

 which it is the Intereſt (let me take the boldneſs to ſay) as well as the Duty-of-Chriſtian Kings and Princes, above all other men, to aſſert and maintain. For by theſe Holy Books their Authority is as ſtrongly ſupported; as by the pretended Traditions of the Roman Church it is notoriouſly undermined and ſubverted. Upon which account it is a point of their greateſt Wiſdom, not only to keep theſe Books in their Peoples hands; but to encourage, nay command the conſcientious reading of them; that they may there learn how plainly they are taught, and how Religiouſly they are bound to fear, honour and obey their Sovereigns, even though they were Pagans; much more when they are Chriſtians. Of which Liberty if they ſuffer their People to be deprived, they ſhall ſoon be taught that they owe no further reſpect to their Princes, than it pleaſes the Biſhop of Rome to allow them. Who from the Dignity of a particular Biſhop and Paſtor of Souls, is raiſed to be a Worldly Monarch, above all Kings and Emperours; by ſewing ſeveral patches and ſhreds to the ancient Chriſtian Doctrine,

 under the Name of Traditions. For nothing is more apparent in Hiſtory than this; that as the Biſhop of Rome's Greatneſs increaſed, ſo Traditions were ſtill more and more multiplyed; which in proceſs of time were more recommended than the Scriptures themſelves, and more Religiouſly obſerved.
